The '''vertical mattress stitch''' is a [[surgical suture|suture]] type used to close skin [[wound]]s. The advantages of the vertical mattress suture are that it provides closure for both deep and superficial layers, and also allows perfect eversion and vertical opposition of the superficial skin edges.<ref name = zuber/><ref>{{Cite book
